The paper proposes a method for generating polyphonic music using convolutional generative adversarial networks with binary neurons. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely sub-category as the paper specifically deals with generating music. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel method for generating music using deep learning techniques. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses convolutional GANs, which are a type of deep learning model. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using objective measures to evaluate the generated music. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses binary neurons in the refiner network.
